Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the annual cost of cybercrime and reviews the recent developments in Exploit Kit capability, which are both related to cybersecurity.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the production line of the cybercrime economy, which involves the development and deployment of software.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper discusses the impact of cybercrime on the global economy and society.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the use of distributed systems in Exploit Kit deployment.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper may discuss the use of social engineering techniques in Exploit Kit deployment.
